üòõOver the years I‚Äôve experimented with many different types of DIY lash growth serums and while I still love those .. I have FINALLY PERFECTED the recipe.. especially for these COLD DRY months

üôáüèΩ‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏èJust like the hair on our head, our lashes can get dry and brittle from excessive mascara use, eyeliner, false lashes, glue and from the cold. YOU HAVE TO TAKE CARE of your lashes!!!

üò¨Im not giving EXACT measurements because everyones STORAGE JAR can be different sizes.. mines humungous cuz I use this night and day. So, I‚Äôll tell you HOW MUCH of your jar needs to be full of what .
üëáüèΩWHAT YOU NEED:
‚úÖ1/3 OF YOUR JAR should be JAMAICAN BLACK CASTOR OIL
‚úÖ2/3 ALOE VERA GEL - I USE IT FRESH FROM THE PLANT ‚Ä¶ I like to use a knife to gently scrape the gel because if you put the aloe in a blender it makes it more watery and Im looking for a gel consistency ‚úÖ2 VITAMIN E CAPSULES - use a sanitized safety pin to poke a hole and squeeze the liquid out
.
üíÉüèΩYOU HAVE TO SHAKE THE BOTTLE EVERY-TIME YOU USE IT TO MIX UP THE INGREDIENTS
STORING THIS IN THE FRIDGE MAKES IT LAST LONGER
.
üôäIm showing you 3 different ways to apply this
üï∑1 - with a silicone mascara wand .. I get these from Sallys
üëÄ2 - with a regular mascara wand .. I also get these from Sallys

üí¶A LITTLE GOES A LONG WAY.. dont DRENCH your lashes thinking that it‚Äôll make them grow faster.. you‚Äôll just end up getting it in your eyes and find it annoying.
